1846. Maximum Element After Decreasing and Rearranging

Intuition:
As we are asked to find maximum element in the array after all the operations
to make array satisfy the given conditions.
let us go throught the conditions first

1.The value of the first element in arr must be 1.
So,regardless of what element is in the 0th index 
we will change it to 1.
2.The absolute difference between any 2 adjacent elements 
must be less than or equal to 1. 
we will check the difference between arr[i] and arr[i-1] as we know 0th index 
must be 1 we will start the loop from 1 instead 0 

Operations can be performed:
* Decrease the value of any element of arr to a smaller positive integer.
* Rearrange the elements of arr to be in any order.

test case:
Input: arr = [2,2,1,2,1]
Output: 2
Explanation: 
We can satisfy the conditions by rearranging arr so it becomes [1,2,2,2,1].
The largest element in arr is 2.

Approach:
Sorting is required . 
Sort the array then we can greedly check at each index for the max element
if the difference between ith element and i-1th element is not less or equal to one
then we make ith element as i-1th element+1 that arr[i]=arr[i-1]+1;
which will give us the required difference 


Code:
class Solution {
    public int maximumElementAfterDecrementingAndRearranging(int[] arr) {
        int n=arr.length;
    Arrays.sort(arr);
    int max=1;
    if(arr[0]!=1){
        arr[0]=1;
    }
    for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
        if(arr[i]-arr[i-1]>1){
            arr[i]=arr[i-1]+1;
        }
        max=Math.max(max,arr[i]);
    }
    return max;

        
    }
   
}



